# Template for environment files — copy to .env.<environment> and fill in, then encrypt:
#   cp .env.example .env.dev   (set values)   &&   npm run env:encrypt
#
# DEPLOY_ENV is required and must be one of: prod | staging | dev | test
DEPLOY_ENV=

# Add real secrets/config below. After editing, run `npm run env:encrypt`
# so the committed .env.<environment> file only ever contains ciphertext.
# Example:
# SOME_API_KEY=
